description:
You are an energy policy researcher. Compile a comparative snapshot of energy metrics for Texas (TX), California (CA), and West Virginia (WV) using the U.S. Energy Information Administration (EIA) website (https://www.eia.gov/state/). For each state, extract the Total Energy Production (in Trillion Btu), Net Electricity Generation Rank, and Average Retail Price of Electricity to the Residential Sector (in cents/kWh) from the latest annual data. Create a Firefox bookmark folder named 'Grid Analysis' containing bookmarks for each state's EIA profile page. Export the data to a JSON report at '~/Documents/energy_comparison.json' with the following structure:

{
  "Texas": {
    "total_production_trillion_btu": <number>,
    "generation_rank": <number>,
    "residential_price_cents": <number>
  },
  "California": {
    "total_production_trillion_btu": <number>,
    "generation_rank": <number>,
    "residential_price_cents": <number>
  },
  "West_Virginia": {
    "total_production_trillion_btu": <number>,
    "generation_rank": <number>,
    "residential_price_cents": <number>
  }
}
